                            <comment id="14112840" author="stack" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2014 21:04:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt; tried this but the circular dependencies killed the effort.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think anyone will disagree with you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=keegan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;keegan&quot;&gt;Keegan Witt&lt;/a&gt;  Have you tried it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14112850" author="keegan" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2014 21:07:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just used IntelliJ to search the usages, I didn&apos;t actually try moving them.  I&apos;ll give it a try when I get a chance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14112991" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 27 Aug 2014 22:44:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IIRC, the big source of circular dependency was HFile. This might be worse now that we have MR over snapshots.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14113174" author="enis" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 01:26:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think what we should do is to decouple hregion + hfile + wal into hbase-storage/hbase-region module. Then we can do the mapreduce module. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14113495" author="eclark" created="Thu, 28 Aug 2014 07:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; That was my thought too when I last looked at how to do this.  HLog seemed like the hardest part of those. And HFile and Store are pretty intertwined so I gave up last time I started looking at this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not a small undertaking but it will pay dividends for the end user. So totally a worth wile thing to do. Let me know if there&apos;s something I can do to help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15014842" author="nkedel" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 00:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Picking this up at the suggestion of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15036441" author="nkedel" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2015 19:37:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is looking bigger, and probably difficult to review especially coming from a relative newb.  I&apos;ve broken things up into subtasks, and this should be easier to review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15037081" author="stack" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2015 02:09:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;These subtasks look great.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15046034" author="nkedel" created="Tue, 8 Dec 2015 00:17:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Initial patch for first subtask is in : &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14910&quot; title=&quot;Create base hbase-mapred and hbase-io modules, move HTableInputFormat and HTableOutputFormat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14910&quot;&gt;HBASE-14910&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
